    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\nWhen calculating illumination with `grdimage` I noted that `-Em` uses _positive counter-clockwise from horizontal_ as reference system while `-Es` uses _positive clockwise from vertical_ as reference.\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n<!-- It helps a lot if you share any data files required to run your script. You can drag-and-drop them here or paste a link to Dropbox/GoogleDrive/etc. -->\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\r\n\r\ngmt grdmath -R-20/20/-20/20 -I0.1 X Y HYPOT DUP 2 MUL PI MUL 8 DIV COS EXCH NEG 10 DIV EXP MUL = sombrero.nc\r\n\r\ngmt grdgradient sombrero.nc -Em0/45 -Glight_Em_0_45.grd\r\ngmt grdgradient sombrero.nc -Es0/45 -Glight_Es_0_45.grd\r\n\r\ngmt grdimage -JX15c sombrero.nc -Ilight_Em_0_45.grd -AEm_0_45.png\r\ngmt grdimage -JX15c sombrero.nc -Ilight_Es_0_45.grd -AEs_0_45.png\r\n\r\n\r\ngmt grdgradient sombrero.nc -Em90/45 -Glight_Em_90_45.grd\r\ngmt grdgradient sombrero.nc -Es90/45 -Glight_Es_90_45.grd\r\n\r\ngmt grdimage -JX15c sombrero.nc -Ilight_Em_90_45.grd -AEm_90_45.png\r\ngmt grdimage -JX15c sombrero.nc -Ilight_Es_90_45.grd -AEs_90_45.png\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Actual outcome**\r\n\r\n**Light Source 0/45**\r\n\r\n`-Es0/45` correct, light source 12 o'clock\r\n![Es_0_45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45796239/113453914-4e0ba500-9407-11eb-97e7-d4bd0eafd1e0.png)\r\n\r\n`-Em0/45` wrong, light source 3 o'clock\r\n![Em_0_45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45796239/113453913-4d730e80-9407-11eb-8cbb-b37548b7767a.png)\r\n\r\n**Light Source 90/45**\r\n\r\n`-Es90/45` right, light source 3 o'clock\r\n![Es_90_45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45796239/113453910-4c41e180-9407-11eb-99e2-dfffe0f03a39.png)\r\n\r\n`-Em90/45` wrong, light source 12 o'clock\r\n![Em_90_45](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45796239/113453917-4ea43b80-9407-11eb-90ea-8714db9ebf99.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected outcome**\r\n\r\nI expected `-Em` behaving the same way `-Es` does \u2013 _positive clockwise from vertical_\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.2.0_c8b9282_2021.03.27\r\n",
